  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.night_heron.title": "Black-crowned Night Heron",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.night_heron.subtitle": "Waterside night fisher",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.night_heron.intro.title": "Note",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.night_heron.intro.body": "By day it passes for a gray branch by the water. After dusk it starts its quiet shift, beating its wings hard at first, then gliding off as if the dark had somewhere to carry it.",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.sparrow.title": "Sparrow",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.sparrow.subtitle": "Little noise under the eaves",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.sparrow.intro.title": "Note",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.sparrow.intro.body": "A sparrow is common, but a village feels wrong without it. It hops, pecks, checks on you, and when crumbs hit the ground one bird pretends to wander over before the rest remember they are busy too.",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.budgerigar.title": "Budgerigar",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.budgerigar.subtitle": "A green noisy cloud over the grass",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.budgerigar.intro.title": "Note",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.budgerigar.intro.body": "At sunrise they burst from the trees like a gust of green wind, then spend the day nosing through grass seeds. When music starts, a few simply cannot resist swaying along.",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.spotted_dove.title": "Spotted Dove",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.spotted_dove.subtitle": "A soft weather call at field edges",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.spotted_dove.intro.title": "Note",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.spotted_dove.intro.body": "Most of the day it walks slowly on the ground, pecking once or twice before lifting its head to coo. When weather begins to turn, its voice grows scarce, as if it heard the rain before you did.",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.pigeon.title": "Pigeon",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.pigeon.subtitle": "A familiar face between roofs and squares",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.pigeon.intro.title": "Note",
  "gui.neoguanniao.bird_guide.entry.pigeon.intro.body": "Gray or white, it is perfectly comfortable beside human buildings. It takes its time, walking, pecking, and occasionally fluttering to a new spot before resuming the same routine.",
